    • Field Detail

      • NEXT

        @Deprecated
public static final java.lang.String NEXT
        Deprecated. 
        Name of "next" parameter.

        Removed from the CS's protocols.

        Used by third parties to redirect users after an OAuth call. Per CS rules.

        This parameter should be embedded into the authorization URLs, as a regular parameter.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • REDIRECT

        public static final java.lang.String REDIRECT
        Used to internally redirect users.

        Used internally to redirect users after an OAuth call.

        This parameter is similar to next, as it is destined to perform redirections made by the local server that originated the OAuth calls. next was used the redirect clients coming from CS, after an OAuth login operation, but was removed from the protocol.

        On normal circumstances, this parameter should be preferred as it allows the server to control redirection with more flexibility. Additionally, redirection can occur faster, and more efficiently.

        This parameter should be embedded into the callback URLs.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
